- if any_sites?
  .col-md-3= render 'side'
%div{class: any_sites? ? 'col-md-9' : ''}
  .welcome
    %h1 
      Hey, welcome to 
      = logo_big
      %span.hermes-title Hermes
      = ":)"
  .explain
    %ul
      %li
        To set up Hermes for your website:
        %ul
          %li 
            add the following code to your pages just before the ending
            %code &lt;/body&gt;
            tag and <b>before</b> your page scripts:
            .embed-element
              %pre#embed_static
                &lt;script src="#{hermes_embed_url}"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
              %button.btn.btn-default.copy-element.btn-xs{:'data-clipboard-target' => "embed_static"}
                %i.fa.fa-files-o
                copy
          %li 
            or you can dinamically import it via JavaScript:
            .embed-element
              %pre#embed_dynamic
                (function(d,l,s){s=d.createElement('script'),l=d.scripts[0];s.src='#{hermes_embed_url}';l.parentNode.insertBefore(s,l)}(document));
              %button.btn.btn-default.copy-element.btn-xs{:'data-clipboard-target' => "embed_dynamic"}
                %i.fa.fa-files-o
                copy
      %li
        Then
        %p.text-center
          = link_to '#new-site-modal', class: 'btn btn-primary btn-lg', :'data-toggle' => 'modal' do
            Add new site
  .explain
    %p
      Once you added a site, you can add messages as you wish to it: they will be shown to your visitor until they dismiss them.
    %p
      You can decide, for every single message:
    %ul
      %li the publishing time frame
      %li the visualization order (for multiple messages on one page)
      %li the layout type (broadcast message or tooltip bound to a specific page element)
